# S02-T02: Device Enumeration & Switching

## Objective
Enumerate connected video input devices and provide a hot-switch mechanism without UI flicker.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `CameraService.listDevices(): Promise<CameraDevice[]>` returns id, label, kind, facingMode hint.
- Zustand `useCameraStore` holds: `devices`, `activeDeviceId`, `setActive(id)`.
- `mediadevices.ondevicechange` triggers store refresh.
- Switching device closes prior stream and opens new one within one render frame.

## Steps
1. Extend `CameraService` with `listDevices`.
2. Create `useCameraStore` (Zustand) at `src/features/video/state/cameraStore.ts`.
3. Wire `ondevicechange` listener (bound at app boot).
4. Expose `useCameras()` hook returning sorted device list.

## Invariants
- Device list never empty if at least one device exists (force refresh on permission grant).
- Switching is atomic — no intermediate "no stream" state visible to UI.
- Permission re-prompt suppressed once granted in session.
